reviewText: Classic movie!!  Looks great on Blu Ray!!  Happy to add this blu ray to my collection. Also just to clarify this version of the Blu Ray DOES include a title page like other blu rays where u can select: Play movie, Bonus Features, scene selection, and setup.
It's Disney - what else need to be said
The musical with Robin Williams remains funny and enchanting . Great for kids and whimsical adults. Disney often stops production of their films so get it now if you want it.

Great movie but don't like the format.  With other DVDs and Blu Rays you are prompted to start the movie where you left off or start from the beginning - this one doesn't allow for that.  If this is a feature you need, like our family does, then skip this format.
Can't go wrong with this movie and it was new in box as I ordered it.
Love the movie have since I was a kid
It was not new although it was priced like it was new, it does not work, restarts on chapter 15. Tried 4 ti.es before my husband said it was trash!
Such a great movie. Fun for everyone.

Works just fine, North America EST zone. I did notice some coloring off... one of the street vendors, towards the beginning,  when Jasmine gives a kid an apple... the vendor's hat (part of the hat) appears to be colored the same as his skin... Not sure if original defect or this version... Regardless, movie plays, works great, my kid's happy and its not priced at a ridiculous amount like many of the other classics.
Works great. Has a ton of languages to choose from, but one of them is English so works for me.
Luv it, a must for the home library
Kids loved it!! It is neat to watch it on bluray !! It was like going back to my childhood watching it but now its even better!! You can't go wrong with Disney.
It met my expectations. It's the original - nothing added or taken away or adjusted.
Did not play on my Blu-ray player. Run time on the screen title is different from run time on the back of the dvd. I will be returning.
